Dia. 03 Opponent's Vital Point
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par Black's block at 1 ignores the question of the life and death problem.
\par White is satisfied after living with 2.
\par
\par If Black plays hane at A instead of 1, Black lives again with 2. The 1-2 point was the vital point in this case. Moreover "\cf1\b the opponent's vital point is my vital point proverb\cf0\b0 " was useful again.
\par
\par }
